                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The fix is applied in revision 4576.\n\nThere is no case-folding applied to the column name in the key of the array returned by describeTable().  The reason for this is that the case is significant, because column names are commonly delimited in SQL generated from Zend_Db classes.",
